"Right I'm fairly sure this is at the loch lomond birds of prey centre and they deserve lots of credit. This bird was given to them as a last chance before it was put to sleep. It was so unmanageable and so many people had tried and failed to look after it. But the llbopc work their magic and saved the bird. It now takes part in shows and is very entertaining to watch. The bird does so much weird stuff in its enclosure that there is a sign up to tell visitors that the bird is ok that it's not in distress. He lies on his back, chases shadows and rolls around. But in the shows he does so much cool stuff."</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Jpmlfi8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[NuddelNinja]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>beware the snides of Mars</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/tWL4PBd</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KMfKJUf.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/tWL4PBd</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ngugi]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Crowd work Jeff Arcuri</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XAHFUbN</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/U3YEIRh.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mnnBKEm.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3HG8PUp.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hN1f79Q.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vmBhc6L.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vLgRJws.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>"It sounds like Sarah owns Ringo and Amber"</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XAHFUbN</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MileysVirus]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Orange cat be like: wth just happened?!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/UrSFHxA</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xKkbag1.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/UrSFHxA</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[TheWhatever666]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Imgur asked me to share something on my cake day, so I share this!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/wMlVMHx</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/uKmpQey.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I made this upside down apple pumpkin cake for Thanksgiving!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eZLfQtS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zvHAxR5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Ingredients
1 Granny Smith
1 Honeycrisp
About 2.5 oz Butter
3/4 cup Brown sugar
3 Tbsp cold tap water
1 tsp vanilla
1 tsp fine sea salt (I used Diamond baking salt)
2 cups all purpose flour, I used Gold Medal Blue
1 1/2 cups granulated sugar
1 tsp baking soda 
2 tsp baking powder
1 Tbsp pumpkin pie spice mix
1/2 tsp fine sea salt
3 large eggs, room temp
1 cup vegetable oil
1 can or 15 oz of Libby’s pure pumpkin

Recipe
-preheat your oven to 350F
-peel, core and cut your apples into wedges (each piece should be about an 1/8th size)
-whisk together the dry ingredients: flour, sugar, baking soda and powder, pumpkin pie spice and salt in a large bowl 
-now in a separate bowl, whisk your wet ingredients: eggs, oil, and pumpkin
-in a medium saucepan, add the water and brown sugar together on medium heat to melt the sugar. Bring to simmer, add the butter and continuously whisk (be quick here so as to not let the pan overflow) until the caramel reduces and it will coat the back of a spoon. Add salt and vanilla to finish.
-take the pan off heat and toss your apples in to coat them, then place the apples at the bottom of a round cake pan until the surface is covered (be sure not to overcrowd it though)
-pour the remains of the saucepan over the apples
-whisk your cake’s wet and dry ingredients together and then pour over the apples
-bake for about 35-45 minutes or until a toothpick poked in the center comes out clean. You can also temp the center of the cake, goal is 200-210F. Another technique is to gently press the center and see if it bounces back. If you have left an indentation, it’s not ready.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/wMlVMHx</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[cupidsmoke]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Biden announces new policy</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zNXn3F2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/b1Vz6av.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZVgb0qP.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://www.reuters.com/business/healthcare-pharmaceuticals/us-sets-policy-seize-government-funded-drug-patents-if-price-deemed-too-high-2023-12-07/?utm_source=reddit.com&utm_source=reddit.com

